# VoteChain AI Service Rules

Identity verification microservice at `ai-service/`. Called by the Node.js backend via HTTP — never directly by Flutter.

## Stack

- **Python FastAPI**
- **EasyOCR** — CNIC/document text extraction
- **DeepFace** — face recognition and matching
- **OpenCV** — image preprocessing and liveness checks

## Service Separation

Each capability is an independent module — never combine in a single monolithic handler:

```
ai-service/
├── app/
│   ├── main.py              # FastAPI app entry point
│   ├── routers/
│   │   ├── ocr.py           # OCR endpoints
│   │   ├── face.py          # Face recognition endpoints
│   │   └── liveness.py      # Liveness detection endpoints
│   ├── services/
│   │   ├── ocr_service.py
│   │   ├── face_service.py
│   │   └── liveness_service.py
│   ├── models/              # Pydantic request/response schemas
│   └── utils/               # Image processing helpers
```

| Service | Responsibility |
|---------|---------------|
| **OCR Service** | Extract CNIC number and name from document images |
| **Face Recognition Service** | Match live face against registered reference photo |
| **Liveness Detection** | Detect spoofing (photos, screens, masks) |

## Rules

- Return **structured JSON responses** only — no HTML, no file downloads to client.
- **No frontend logic** — this service has no UI concerns.
- **No blockchain logic** — never interact with Ethereum directly.
- **No database business logic** — backend persists results; AI service is stateless.
- **Document every endpoint** — FastAPI auto-docs + docstrings on all route handlers.
- Handle model loading errors gracefully with clear HTTP status codes.

## Standard AI Response Format

Every endpoint must return structured JSON in this shape. Use Pydantic response models — never return raw dicts or plain strings.

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "confidence": 99.2,
  "data": {
    "name": "",
    "cnic": "",
    "dob": ""
  }
}
```

```python
# ✅ OCR success
{
    "success": True,
    "confidence": 99.2,
    "data": {
        "name": "Ali Khan",
        "cnic": "12345-1234567-1",
        "dob": "1998-04-15"
    }
}

# ✅ Face match success
{
    "success": True,
    "confidence": 97.5,
    "data": {
        "matched": True,
        "distance": 0.23
    }
}

# ✅ Failure
{
    "success": False,
    "confidence": 42.1,
    "data": {
        "matched": False,
        "reason": "FACE_MISMATCH"
    }
}
```

Define one Pydantic `BaseResponse` schema in `app/models/responses.py` and extend per endpoint.

## Security

- Accept images via multipart upload — validate file type and size before processing.
- Never log or persist raw biometric images — process in memory, return results, discard.
- Do not expose model internals or file paths in error messages.

## Anti-Patterns

```python
# ❌ Mixing OCR and face logic in one endpoint
@router.post("/verify")
async def verify(file: UploadFile):
    ocr_result = easyocr_reader.read(file)  # mixed concerns
    face_result = deepface.verify(file)     # mixed concerns

# ❌ Direct MongoDB access
from pymongo import MongoClient
db.users.insert_one({...})
```
